</i> (  see  Clement  ) or an abstract noun meaning ‘mercy’. It was fairly popular in Britain from the late medieval period until the 17th century, but has since been used less often."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Clemence Luxembourg was born in 1360, in Lutzelhouse, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France, her father, Raul De Luxembourg, was 41 and her mother, Walpurg Von Lützelstein, was 31. She married Gille de Luxembourg in 1378, in Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1411, in Picardie, France, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1360–Abt 1411":"1360–umbes 1411","1360–1411":"1360–1411","1355–1404":"1355–1404","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1320–1367":"1320–1367","1330–1406":"1330–1406","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Abt 1367":"umbes 1367","1382":"1382","Abt 1411":"umbes 1411","1404":"1404","1378":"1378","1367":"1367","1411":"1411","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","Lutzelhouse, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Lutzelhouse, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa","Luxembourg City, Lëtzebuerg, Luxembourg, Luxembourg":"Luxembourg City, Luxembourg City, Luxembourg, Luksemburg","Ulcombe, Kent, England":"Ulcombe, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Otterden, Kent, England":"Otterden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1360–Abt 1411":"1360–noin 1411","1360–1411":"1360–1411","1355–1404":"1355–1404","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1320–1367":"1320–1367","1330–1406":"1330–1406","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Abt 1367":"noin 1367","1382":"1382","Abt 1411":"noin 1411","1404":"1404","1378":"1378","1367":"1367","1411":"1411","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","Lutzelhouse, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Lutzelhouse, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska","Luxembourg City, Lëtzebuerg, Luxembourg, Luxembourg":"Luxembourg City, Luxembourg City, Luxembourg, Luxemburg","Ulcombe, Kent, England":"Ulcombe, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Ranska","Otterden